### Description of Change ###

_Note: This was originally PR #2201 from dkarzon; recreating it in an attempt to address a CI build issue_ 

This change makes the Android Date and Time picker renderers easier to customise by virtualising the function that creates the dialog allowing custom dialogs to be used. The most common usage of this will be to add custom buttons to the dialogs.

    // Creates a Date picker dialog with a clear button
    public class DatePickerDialogWithClear : DatePickerDialog
    {
        EventHandler<DateSetEventArgs> _callBack;

        public DatePickerDialogWithClear(Context context, EventHandler<DateSetEventArgs> callBack, int year, int monthOfYear, int dayOfMonth)
            : base(context, callBack, year, monthOfYear, dayOfMonth)
        {
            _callBack = callBack;
            SetButton((int)DialogButtonType.Neutral, "Clear", (sender, args) =>
            {
                _callBack(this, new DateSetEventArgsWithClear());
            });
        }
    }


### API Changes ###

Added:
 - protected virtual TimePickerDialog CreateTimePickerDialog

Changed:
 - void CreateDatePickerDialog -> protected virtual DatePickerDialog CreateDatePickerDialog

### Behavioral Changes ###

This has no changes for existing apps but will allow developers to more easily extend the Date and Time pickers on Android.

